728134f-c.text: Utopia Parkway, west die, near 75th Avenue, showing the old Black Stump Hotel. It was owned at one time by Benthin, then by Dietz and later by one Klein, who tore it down in 1933. Mr. Armbruster states that this place may have been Ryerson's Inn during the Revolution where the Nenis Jager Corps under Captain (?)issker was quartered. Views 1,2,3: 1922. View 4: 1929.

728135f-a.text:
Utopia Parkway, west side, north from 75th Avenue.  The second and third houses were owned by H. Miller in 1873.  Mr. Eugene L. Ambruster, a collector of Queens photographs, states that the third house may have been Nyerson's Inn of
Black Stump during the Revolution.

March 31, 1927
